Build and installs private versions of 3rd-party packages.

Usage: ./build-contrib.sh [OPTION]... [FILE]...

Install bdesc packages
  -i set install destination
  -t target system (use for cross-compiling)
  -a target CPU architecture (use for cross-comiling)
  -c continue building after error
  -h display this help and exit

To build individual packages separately call

  ./build-contrib.sh package.bdesc

Verbose build output is written to the log file under build/build.log.
